M|Use |**Im|lo-md (eliminates intermediate array)**
M|Use |tx|Chaining `.map().filter(Boolean)` creates an intermediate array and iterates twice. Use `.flatMap()` to transform and filter in a single pass.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```ts
M|Use |tx|const userNames = us
M|Use |.map|null)
M|Use |tx|.filter(Boolean)
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```ts
M|Use |tx|const userNames = us.flatMap(us =>
M|Use |user|[]
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Mo|**
M|Use |tx|```ts
M|Use |tx|// Extract valid emails from rp
M|Use |tx|// Before
M|Use |tx|const emails = rp
M|Use |.map|null)
M|Use |tx|.filter(Boolean)
M|Use |tx|// After
M|Use |tx|const emails = rp.flatMap(r =>
M|Use |r.su|[]
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|// Parse and filter valid numbers
M|Use |tx|// Before
M|Use |tx|const numbers = strings
M|Use |tx|.map(s => parseInt(s, 10))
M|Use |tx|.filter(n => !isNaN(n))
M|Use |tx|// After
M|Use |tx|const numbers = strings.flatMap(s => {
M|Use |tx|const n = parseInt(s, 10)
M|Use |retu|[n]
M|Use |tx|})
M|Use |tx|```
